 2678                                                       ;The next subroutine perforins a double transfer opera-
 2679                                                       ;tion. It first transfers the contents of the FPACC into
 2680                                                       ;the FPOP. It then transfers new data (as pointed to by
 2681                                                       ;H & L upon entry to the subroutine) into the FPACC.
 2682                     
 2683  11C9  CD D8 11     FACXOP:	CALL SAVEHL                     ;Save contents of H & L upon entry to subroutine
 2684  11CC  21 1F 00     	LXI H,FPACC                     ;Set pointer to FPACC LSW
 2685  11CF  CD C1 11     	CALL OPLOAD                     ;Transfer FPACC to FPOP
 2686  11D2  CD E7 11     	CALL RESTHL                     ;Recover original subroutine entry values for H & L
 2687  11D5  C3 B1 11     	JMP FLOAD                       ;Transfer registers pointed to by H & L into the FPACC
